  <h3>Project Narrative Components</h3>
  <p>The following sections must be included in the project narrative. Navigate to the chatbot through the toolbar for help crafting a narrative draft.</p>
  <li><strong>Community Vision Description</strong>: Provides an overview of the Project Area, description of challenges faced, and vision for how the grant will respond to advance environmental and climate justice. See <a href="#">Section IV.B</a> for details.</li>
  <li><strong>Climate Action Strategy</strong>: Must include at least one project aligned with the Climate Action Strategies listed in <a href="#">Section I.G.3</a> and <a href="#">Appendix C</a>. Describes how the selected strategy(ies) will address climate resilience and/or GHG reduction challenges.</li>
  <li><strong>Pollution Reduction Strategy</strong>: Must include at least one project aligned with the Pollution Reduction Strategies listed in <a href="#">Section I.G.3</a> and <a href="#">Appendix D</a>. Describes how the selected strategy(ies) will address pollution monitoring, prevention, and remediation challenges.</li>
  <li><strong>Community Engagement and Collaborative Governance Plan</strong>: Describes methods for community engagement throughout the project, measures to mitigate participation barriers, government involvement, and a collaborative governance structure with roles of partners. See <a href="#">Section I.G.3</a> for details.</li>
  <li><strong>Community Strength Plan</strong>: Describes strategies to enhance community economic prosperity, promote inclusive development, drive project benefits to existing residents, and address potential displacement risks. See <a href="#">Section I.G.3</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>Readiness Approach</strong>: Describes how the applicant will initiate grant activities quickly to complete the project within the 3-year period of performance. See <a href="#">Section I.G.3</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>Compliance Plan</strong>: Describes how the applicant will ensure compliance with grant terms/conditions and manage legal/compliance risks. See <a href="#">Section I.G.3</a>.</li>
